1 (b) “District” means a taxing and assessment district.
2 (c) “District council” means the governing body of a county acting as the district
3 council for a district created under this subtitle.
4 (d) “Project” means an erosion prevention project or erosion control project.
5 21–202.
6 This subtitle supplements the provisions of the Natural Resources Article relating to
7 shore erosion control projects.
8 21–203.
9 The purpose of projects constructed under this subtitle is to prevent erosion of land
10 by any body of water in the State.
11 21–204.
12 (a) Each recorded subdivision that abuts a body of water in the State is a district.
13 (b) Each district established under this section shall be named for the subdivision
14 from which the district is created.
15 21–205.
16 (a) The governing body of a county is the district council for each district in the
17 county.
18 (b) A district council shall:
19 (1) keep a separate record of its proceedings for each district; and
20 (2) deposit all money received for each district to the credit of that district.
21 (c) (1) The district council shall:
22 (I) require the depository of money under subsection (b)(2) of this
23 section to give the same security for the repayment of money deposited; and
24 (II) pay the same interest on the money as is required for the deposit
25 of county funds.
26 (2) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS ON MONEY DEPOSITED FOR A DISTRICT
27 SHALL BE CREDITED TO THAT DISTRICT.

